2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1498
4
5 By: Representatives Painter, Ray
6 By: Senator Crowell
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING MILITARY-TYPE
10 CANTEENS AND EXCHANGES; AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
11
12
Subtitle
13
14 TO AMEND THE LAW CONCERNING MILITARY-
15 TYPE CANTEENS AND EXCHANGES.
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
18
19 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 12-63-404(b), concerning the establishment
20 and operations of military-type canteens and exchanges, is amended to read as
21 follows:
22 (b)(1) Except as otherwise provided in subdivision (b)(2) of this section, a
23 military-type canteen and exchange established or operated under this section
24 is subject to similar procedures, policies, privileges, limitations, and
25 restrictions governing the canteens and exchanges of the Army and Air Force
26 Exchange Service, as the Adjutant General may deem advisable, necessary, or
27 expedient.
28 (2)(A) Military-type canteens and exchanges established or operated
29 under this section shall not sell, trade, exchange, market, or vend
30 automobiles, household appliances, furniture, building products, motorcycles,
31 or bicycles.
32 (B) Military-type canteens and exchanges may contract with one (1) or
33 more automobile rental agencies to provide leased or rented vehicles for use
34 by uniformed service members, trainees, and other temporary residents of
35 military reservations.
36
